---
import ToolLayout from '../../layouts/ToolLayout.astro';
import MediaConverter from '../../components/MediaConverter.astro';
---

<ToolLayout slug="aac-converter">
  <MediaConverter slug="aac-converter" />

  <div slot="about" class="flex flex-col gap-4 text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-subtle">
    <p>
      This free AAC converter encodes audio into efficient AAC (.m4a) files — the
      format used by Apple Music, YouTube and modern streaming. Drop in MP3, WAV,
      FLAC, OGG, M4A or the audio track of common video files (MP4, MOV, MKV, WebM
      and more) and get back a compact AAC file. There is no queue and no
      file-size limit.
    </p>
    <p>
      Convert one file or a whole batch at once with drag and drop, then download
      each result individually or grab them all as a single ZIP. Choose the target
      bitrate from 64 kbps (voice) up to 256 kbps, set the sample rate and channel
      layout, or keep the originals. A one-click EBU R128 loudness normalize evens
      out volume across tracks — a step most online converters do not offer.
    </p>
    <p>
      The trim and fade controls let you cut a clip to a start and end point and add
      fade-in or fade-out without a separate editor, and an inline player previews
      the converted audio before you save it. Because the conversion happens on your
      device rather than a remote server, your recordings stay private and nothing is
      retained after you close the tab.
    </p>
  </div>
</ToolLayout>
